title: AFP officer dies after shooting incident
text:
Police officer dies after shooting incident at AFP headquarters Updated February 07, 2017 07:26:13 
A female police officer has died in hospital after a shooting incident at the Australian Federal Police headquarters in Melbourne. 
The woman sustained a gunshot wound at the La Trobe Street building shortly before 6:00pm on Monday. 
She was taken to the Royal Melbourne Hospital in a critical condition and died a short time later. 
AFP Commissioner Andrew Colvin said officers were being supported following the tragedy. 
"My thoughts are with her loved ones and the broader AFP family who are dealing with the loss of one of our own today," he said in a statement. 
"We are offering support to her family and the wider AFP workforce." 
The death is not being treated as suspicious and is being investigated by Victoria Police. 
Anyone needing personal help can contact Lifeline on 13 11 14.
